&lt;p>Understanding &lt;code>async&lt;/code>, &lt;code>await&lt;/code>, and Concurrency in Python — A Simple Tutorial&lt;/p>
&lt;p>If you’re learning Python and find terms like &lt;code>async&lt;/code>, &lt;code>await&lt;/code>, and &lt;code>concurrent tasks&lt;/code> confusing — you’re not alone! This tutorial explains how to write Python code that runs &lt;strong>multiple tasks simultaneously&lt;/strong>, such as reading data from the internet, analyzing logs, and fetching records from a remote server.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>